00:43:42.420 --> 00:43:47.010
You can think of it as the quality
that allows the user to sense

00:43:47.010 --> 00:43:50.860
eloquence and beauty in the interface.

00:43:50.890 --> 00:43:53.740
To do that, of course,
you have to have the

00:43:53.740 --> 00:43:57.210
highest quality imagery,
highest quality icons,

00:43:57.370 --> 00:44:01.940
follow the layout guidelines,
because this is going to produce

00:44:02.010 --> 00:44:06.880
an interface that engages the user,
and is something that the user

00:44:06.880 --> 00:44:09.260
feels very good about using.

00:44:09.260 --> 00:44:11.790
It's not just its appearance, though.

00:44:12.030 --> 00:44:15.170
But to get the appearance right,
make sure that you use

00:44:15.170 --> 00:44:16.860
our Aqua System widgets.

00:44:16.860 --> 00:44:19.760
If you don't,
you won't be getting the ones that

00:44:19.760 --> 00:44:23.610
we spend a lot of time designing
to make sure that they do have the

00:44:23.610 --> 00:44:26.580
highest level of aesthetic integrity.

00:44:26.580 --> 00:44:29.190
And follow the layout guidelines.

00:44:29.440 --> 00:44:31.190
In a minute,
we'll talk about why the layout

00:44:31.190 --> 00:44:32.510
guidelines are so important.

00:44:32.540 --> 00:44:39.960
So again, it's not just the beauty,
it's the composition of the interface.

00:44:40.030 --> 00:44:45.690
The layout guidelines,
combined with our Aqua widgets, provide,

00:44:45.690 --> 00:44:48.220
you know,
they support the control hierarchy,

00:44:48.220 --> 00:44:50.820
they support the, you know,
what's important,

00:44:50.820 --> 00:44:53.510
and help the user to see what's
important in the interface.

00:44:53.540 --> 00:44:55.790
They eliminate clutter.

00:44:55.820 --> 00:44:57.620
You know,
if you have really great features,

00:44:57.670 --> 00:45:01.580
that's nice, but if it's buried in
a bunch of other stuff,

00:45:01.620 --> 00:45:02.980
the user might not see it.

00:45:02.980 --> 00:45:07.750
So the judicious use of white space,
which is documented very well in

00:45:07.750 --> 00:45:10.970
the Aqua interface guidelines,
will help you there.

00:45:11.180 --> 00:45:14.970
And basically,
it's a business of trying to

00:45:14.970 --> 00:45:17.440
keep the interface simple.

00:45:18.040 --> 00:45:21.690
Taking stuff out of the interface that's
only going to be noise to the user and

00:45:21.690 --> 00:45:23.770
distracts the user from their task.

00:45:23.860 --> 00:45:25.740
It's going to provide balance.

00:45:25.780 --> 00:45:30.380
So, and the user can see where, you know,
where everything fits and they can

00:45:30.440 --> 00:45:32.940
find what they need when they need it.

00:45:32.970 --> 00:45:37.140
To do that, you're going to have to apply
these guidelines consistently and

00:45:37.140 --> 00:45:42.810
you're going to have to attend to
a great level of visual detail.

