00:47:18.600 --> 00:47:21.400
The next principle is Simplicity.

00:47:22.410 --> 00:47:24.700
Again,
if the user is trying to get something

00:47:24.700 --> 00:47:27.970
done and they can't figure out how to
do it because there's so much garbage

00:47:28.000 --> 00:47:31.500
on the interface that they can't find
the thing that they need to work on,

00:47:31.830 --> 00:47:36.060
that's going to cause them to not
be able to get their work done.

00:47:36.090 --> 00:47:37.770
They're not going to be very happy.

00:47:37.910 --> 00:47:42.170
So make sure that the basic
features are immediately apparent.

00:47:42.290 --> 00:47:46.000
That way the user can focus on
the task that they're performing.

00:47:46.220 --> 00:47:48.200
Basically, reduce clutter.

00:47:48.340 --> 00:47:50.350
Now, in saying that you should
keep the interface simple,

00:47:50.420 --> 00:47:51.970
you're going to say, "Well,
I've got a lot of advanced

00:47:52.040 --> 00:47:55.420
features I want to give them,
too." Well, you can do that.

00:47:55.520 --> 00:47:56.200
We did it here.

00:47:56.370 --> 00:48:00.510
This is the simple save dialog that shows
them how--provides a place for a name,

00:48:00.660 --> 00:48:04.010
a pop-up for recent and favorite places,
and the button.

00:48:04.140 --> 00:48:09.870
It also has a disclosure button
that allows the user to access

00:48:09.870 --> 00:48:15.270
the more advanced view of the
entire file hierarchy so they can

00:48:15.330 --> 00:48:18.020
save the document someplace other
than the places that are provided.

00:48:18.020 --> 00:48:20.020
And that pop-up menu.

00:48:20.020 --> 00:48:22.010
This is called progressive disclosure.

00:48:22.020 --> 00:48:26.880
And progressive disclosure allows
the user at their own pace to

00:48:27.240 --> 00:48:30.020
discover the advanced features.

00:48:30.020 --> 00:48:32.020
It's not that the features
are hidden from them.

00:48:32.020 --> 00:48:33.940
If you do progressive
disclosure correctly,

00:48:34.010 --> 00:48:37.730
you will make sure that there's
always something visible to the

00:48:37.730 --> 00:48:40.010
user that tells them where to
go to get the advanced function.

00:48:40.020 --> 00:48:42.310
But it says,
"I'm not going to put it all in

00:48:42.310 --> 00:48:45.970
your face at the same time." You can
progressively discover it as you

00:48:45.970 --> 00:48:47.760
mature in using the application.

00:48:47.780 --> 00:48:49.120
Thank you.

